('Website Update', 'Re Create an Account', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Good Evening Cadets,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">I wanted to let you know I recently changed a lot of things on the website (behind the scenes mostly), however you may notice them as you work on it. However, because of these changes I had to dump the database including your accounts ( I saved the information but to you it will look like I got rid of everything ). So what you will need to do now is reach out to Cadet Rodgers or Cadet Thai and they will create an account for you on the website. Please send them your RIN and email and they can set you up. Sorry for the inconvenience!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; text-size-adjust: auto;\">Very Respectfully,</span><br class=\"\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\" /><br class=\"\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\" /><span style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; text-size-adjust: auto;\">//SIGNED//</span><br class=\"\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\" /><span style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; text-size-adjust: auto;\">Joseph W. Messare</span><br class=\"\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\" /><span style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; text-size-adjust: auto;\">Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute</span><br class=\"\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\" /><span style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; text-size-adjust: auto;\">(585) 500-9728</span><br class=\"\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\" /><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; text-size-adjust: auto;\" href=\"mailto:messaj@rpi.edu\">messaj@rpi.edu</a></span></p>', 2, 1, '2019-05-11 02:08:31', NULL),
('RPI Freshman Move In Program', 'Volunteers Needed', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As you know, with Fall semester rapidly approaching, a new wave of IMT will be joining the Detachment. With that, we will be assisting Fraternities, Sororities, and other campus organizations in helping RPI Class of 2023 move-in. RPI move-in date is Saturday 24 August, with a few exceptions on Monday 19 August and Thursday 22 August. This is an outstanding opportunity to meet incoming cadets, if you are in the area, please consider signing up for a two-hour shift. Please refer to the map and put your name down on the spreadsheet below if you can help out.&nbsp; If you have any questions, don\'t hesitate to ask any questions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>UOD: ABUs or PTGs</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1lssyPX_Lwnu4fbs-lf5Y5NN6fTppn6byUdQV9ETeOCg/edit?usp=sharing\">Sign-Up Spreadsheet</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>KATHERINE G. DONOVAN, C/2d Lt, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Cyber Flight Commander</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Communications Squadron&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>donovk5@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(847) 682-0262</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 11, 2, '2019-08-17 18:55:01', NULL),
('Profile Standardization', 'Standardization', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The start of Fall semester is approaching and we need to standardize our directory profiles on the webiste. This is due COB 26 August; below are the guidelines:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the general heading: use your RPI email address, provide your phone number, and provide your position. If you don\'t have a posistion yet, leave it as \"N/A\" and update it immediately after receiving one. A profile picture is required.</p>\r\n<p>There will be no abbreviations when updating your major. Write your major as listed by your respective university. Cadets with more than one major will input them in alphabetical order, seperated by commas.</p>\r\n<p>Ex:</p>\r\n<p>Email: Johnsmith@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>Phone Number: (123) 456-7891</p>\r\n<p>Major: Aerospace, Computer and Systems, and Electrical Engineering</p>\r\n<p>Position: \"N/A\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Provide a minimum of 3 \"Air Force Goals\" you may have. These goals should focus on ROTC. Each goal should be bulleted with a single hyphen.</p>\r\n<p>Ex:</p>\r\n<p>- Max out the PFA score</p>\r\n<p>- Become Wing Commander</p>\r\n<p>- Receive a pilot slot</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Provide a minimum of 3 \"Personal Goals\" that you plan to achieve outside of ROTC. Each goal should be bulleted with a single hyphen.</p>\r\n<p>Ex:</p>\r\n<p>- Maintain a 4.0 GPA</p>\r\n<p>- Wake up at 0600 everyday</p>\r\n<p>- Be able to rent out an apartment</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Provide a minimum of 1 \"Awards and Achievements\" related to ROTC with a max of 5. Each achievement should be bulleted with a single hyphen and placed in order of personal importance. If possible, state the year of achievement in parenthesis at the end of each bullet.</p>\r\n<p>Ex:</p>\r\n<p>- Selected to become a Combat Rescue Officer (2018)</p>\r\n<p>- Air Force Association Award (2018)</p>\r\n<p>- Field Training Distinguished Graduate (2017)</p>\r\n<p>- Warrior Spirit Award (2016)</p>\r\n<p>- Placed 3rd in Flight Drill at RPIMEC (2018)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the \"Bio\", try to include things not included elsewhere in your profile. Be creative and professional, at a minimum of 3 sentences.</p>\r\n<p>Ex:</p>\r\n<p>I\'m from Galveston, Texas and I attend RPI for physics. I enjoy watching sci-fi shows, hanging out with friends and chatting about science. I\'m very motivated in being the best I can be at whatever I do.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If there are any questions, feel free to ask.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respecfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>PHU T. THAI, C/3C, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Cyber Flight</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Communications Squadron</p>\r\n<p>thaip@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(315) 420 -7868</p>', 5, 3, '2019-08-20 20:04:43', NULL),
('Fundraising Opportunity', 'Fundraising Opportunity', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Cadets,</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">We have been approached with two fundraising opportunities from Sodexo. These pay $12.75 per hour and a free meal is provided at the event. The dates and details are as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">Tuesday, August 27<sup>th</sup>, at the Troy Riverfront for the Welcomefest Picnic for the incoming freshman class.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">Shift is 1500 &ndash; 2100</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">Saturday, September 7<sup>th</sup>, at RPI for the Rensselaer Medalist Day</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">Shifts are 0600 &ndash; 1200 and 0900 &ndash; 1500</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">If you are interested in volunteering, contact Ms. Fredericks with the date and shift you are available.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">These are great opportunities to earn money for the detachment to allow us to pursue extra training opportunities.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">Very Respectfully,</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">IAN A. MORIARTY, C/2d Lt,&nbsp; AFROTC</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">Special Projects Flight Commander</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">550th AFROTC Mission Support Group</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">moriai@rpi.edu</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">(413)824-5286</span></p>', 20, 4, '2019-08-25 22:27:16', NULL),
