('Phase 0 PT', 'Alternative Thursday PT', '<p><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Cadets,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Starting this upcoming Thursday 05 September 19 will start the first Phase 0 PT. There will be minimum standards to get in to the program such as a minimum PFA score of 90 to enter however until that test takes place all are welcome. This will be a prepatory course for Air Force Special Operations. However, for most of you who are not interested in Air Force Special Ops this will just be a very intense PT which will count as a substitiute PT for Thursday\'s PT. It will take place at the same time and place as Thursday\'s PT and for the first event we will start at the Armory at 0630. Please be there slightly before 0630 to stretch because the workout will begin at 0630. If you plan on attending the first session please reach out to me on group me or send me an email and I will add you to the website group which will be where I post the location of each workout (as it may change week to week). Also if you have any questions feel free to reach out to me.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"ApplePlainTextBody\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">--</span><br /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Very Respectfully,</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/Lt Col, AFROTC</span><br /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">Inspector General</span><br /><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">550th Training Squadron</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"ApplePlainTextBody\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">messaj@rpi.edu</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"ApplePlainTextBody\" style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; text-size-adjust: auto;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times; font-size: 12pt;\">(585) 500-9728</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 2, 7, '2019-08-30 18:23:06', NULL),
('First Term Cadet Center', 'First Term Cadet Center', '<pre style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 12px; color: #333333; background-color: #ffffff; white-space: pre-wrap !important;\">Good Evening to our newest Cadets,\r\n\r\nCongratulations! You have all taken the first step in embarking on an incredible adventure that will ultimately lead to becoming a Second Lieutenant in the world\'s greatest Air Force. I am Cadet Rogers. I will be your First Term Cadet Center (FTCC) instructor and flight commander. FTCC is an introductory course into Air Force ROTC and is how we incorporate new cadets into our detachment. FTCC is a non-mandatory event. You are not required to attend. However, if you are serious about your future as an ROTC cadet, I highly suggest you attend. You will learn customs and courtesies, how to properly wear blues, airman battle uniform, and the detachment polo and khakis uniform, wing structure, chain of command, Air Force and Navy ranks, how to properly format operational orders, memorandums and emails, and warrior knowledge. FTCC is only 40 minutes before physical training (PT). Since physical training is mandatory, it is truly convenient and in your best interest to attend FTCC. Below I\'ve compiled a list of items to bring for your first day of ROTC, a campus map of RPI, and a schedule.\r\n\r\nFTCC class will begin at 6 am this Wednesday. Please eat a light meal prior to leaving your dorms/homes, as there will not be another chance to eat until dismissal from Leadership Laboratory at 10:00 am. FTCC class will be held in the Rensselaer Union on the third floor in room 3202. Please arrive by 5:50 am. We will be going over introductions and customs and courtesies. Please wear your workout clothes (described below) to class, as we will be leaving to go to physical training after class is over. Physical training (PT) will include: sprinting and calisthenics. Ensure you are well hydrated and stretched prior to PT. Once PT is over, you will have 20 minutes to get changed out of your workout gear into your detachment polo and khakis. We will then walk over to Leadership Laboratory (LLAB) which will be held in Low 4050. You will all be dismissed at 10:00am.\r\n\r\nTentative Schedule:\r\nParking is available on 15th street or in the Mueller Center Parking Lot\r\n5:50 am Arrive at classroom 3202 on the 3rd floor of the Rensselaer Union\r\n6:00 am First Term Cadet Center (FTCC) Class Begins\r\n6:40 am FTCC Class ends. Walk as a group to the Armory\r\n6:45 am Physical Training Begins\r\n7:30 am Physical Training Ends\r\n7:50 am Arrive at Leadership Laboratory (LLAB) in Low 4050\r\n8:00 am LLAB Begins\r\n10:00 am LLAB Ends\r\n\r\nItems needed:\r\nPen/pencil\r\nNotebook\r\nWorkout clothes\r\nBlack Shorts and a Grey T-shirt (no logos or designs; if you don\'t have the correct color clothes indicated don\'t worry for now)\r\nRunning Shoes\r\nWater-bottle\r\nSnack (ex. Granola bar)\r\nDetachment Polo and Khakis (black polo if you don\'t have a detachment polo)\r\nBelt (matching color of shoes)\r\nDress Shoes (Black sneakers if you don\'t have dress shoes).<br /><br /><a href=\"https://info.rpi.edu/map\">Map of RPI</a>\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to email me. I look forward to meeting you all and kicking off a great semester.\r\n\r\n\r\nVery Respectfully,\r\n\r\n-- \r\nJOHN S. ROGERS, C/2nd Lt, AFROTC\r\nCommander, Bravo Flight\r\n550th AFROTC Training Squadron\r\n<a style=\"color: #0186ba;\" href=\"mailto:rogerj9@rpi.edu\">rogerj9@rpi.edu</a>\r\n603-748-6495\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 26, 8, '2019-09-01 23:54:16', NULL),
('24th Annual Run to Remember', 'Run to Remember', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The 24th Annual Run to Remember will be taking place on Saturday, 14 September at 0900. &nbsp;This run is held every year in support of all MIAs and POWs with all proceeds going toward the Wounded Warrior Project. &nbsp;Run to Remember honors RPI graduate 1Lt Jon Kohl who survived a helicopter crash while he was deployed to Afghanistan. &nbsp;The Wounded Warrior Project has profoundly impacted the Kohl family and continues to provide support to other heroes like 1Lt Kohl. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Share the registration link and flyer with family members, friends, and anyone else who you think might be interested. &nbsp;The second page is attached to the flyer to provide more information on the purpose of the run. &nbsp;All cadets should be at the race - either running or volunteering. &nbsp;If you are not able to participate or volunteer on the day of the race, please reach out to me with your prior commitment. &nbsp;I hope to see you all there! &nbsp;If you have any questions, feel free to contact me. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Registration Link :&nbsp;<a href=\"https://runtoremember.redpodium.com/run-to-remember-2019\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto, RobotoDraft, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">https://runtoremember.redpodium.com/run-to-remember-2019</span> </span></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Vkky_rW0KEFR5cV7_yHqEQjj0S6GWSYT/view?usp=sharing\">Volunteer Spreadsheet</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://rpi.box.com/s/sihhp9wazygipixap5li61k6uba1gzwh\">2019 Flyer</a></p>\r\n<pre style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 12px; caret-color: #333333; color: #333333; white-space: pre-wrap !important;\"><span class=\"sig\" style=\"color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><br />-- \r\nVery Respectfully,\r\n\r\nSTEPHANIE R. HAND, C/Capt, AFROTC\r\nCommander, Training Support Squadron\r\n550th AFROTC Training Support Squadron\r\nhands@rpi.edu\r\n(518)-683-3507</span></pre>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 17, 9, '2019-09-02 20:46:16', NULL),
