://sites.google.com/site/det550runtoremember/flyer\">2019 Flyer</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; caret-color: #212529; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; font-size: 16px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<pre style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow: auto; color: #333333; padding: 0px; caret-color: #333333; white-space: pre-wrap !important;\"><span class=\"sig\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />-- \r\nVery Respectfully,\r\n\r\nSTEPHANIE R. HAND, C/Capt, AFROTC\r\nCommander, Training Support Squadron\r\n550th AFROTC Training Support Squadron\r\nhands@rpi.edu\r\n(518)-683-3507</span></pre>', 17, 33, '2019-09-11 22:15:39', NULL),
('Detachment Fall Picnic ', 'Detachment Fall Picnic ', '<p>AS 100 and AS 250 cadets welcome to Detachment 550! AS 200s and POC welcome back! At the start of each semester Moral, Welfare, and Recreation (MWR) Flight hosts an informal event to encourage the integration of our new members into the Cadet Wing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This semester we will be having a picnic at Prospect Park on Saturday, September 14, 2019, from 1100 to 1400. This is promptly after the Run to Remember, and I encouraged cadets to participate in or volunteer for the run before coming to the park for food and games. The park is about a 15-minute walk from the RPI Armory or about a 5-minute drive. If you plan to attend, please fill out THIS FORM and pay me $5.00 cash or Venmo (@hannah-enggasser) by COB Friday, September 13, 2019, to cover the cost of food and drinks.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a non-mandatory but SUPER FUN event, and you should be wearing civilian attire if you choose to attend.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>HANNAH J. ENGGASSER, C/2nd Lt, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Commander, MWR Flight</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Support Squadron</p>\r\n<p>enggah@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(215)313-9983</p>', 42, 34, '2019-09-11 23:43:53', NULL),
