('Detachment Fall Picnic', 'Detachment Fall Picnic ', '<p>Detachment Fall Picnic</p>\r\n<p>AS 100 and AS 250 cadets welcome to Detachment 550! AS 200s and POC welcome back! At the start of each semester Moral, Welfare, and Recreation (MWR) Flight hosts an informal event to encourage the integration of our new members into the Cadet Wing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This semester we will be having a picnic at Prospect Park on Saturday, September 14, 2019, from 1100 to 1400. This is promptly after the Run to Remember, and I encouraged cadets to participate in or volunteer for the run before coming to the park for food and games. The park is about a 15-minute walk from the RPI Armory or about a 5-minute drive. If you plan to attend, please fill out THIS FORM and pay me $5.00 cash or Venmo (@hannah-enggasser) by COB Friday, September 13, 2019, to cover the cost of food and drinks.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a non-mandatory but SUPER FUN event, and you should be wearing civilian attire if you choose to attend.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>DANIEL B. GARZA, C/3C, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>ALPHA FLIGHT</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Training Squadron</p>\r\n<p>garzad@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(413)272-9954</p>', 42, 37, '2019-09-13 00:42:19', NULL),
('det550.com is now Live', 'New Domain', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I am pleased to announce that we are now officially switching off of the union server and onto our own thanks to the help from Arnold Air Society (AAS). The website is now significantly faster and will stop going down sporadically.</p>\r\n<p>From now on this will be the official website. All data has been transferred over except for profile pictures; the suspense to reupload your profile pictures is COB Monday. Please take this time to review and update all information regarding your profile.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have any issues please contact Cadet Thai.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>New Website: det550.com</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">NOTE: This message must be Read and Understood by COB 16 September 19.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>KATHERINE G. DONOVAN, C/2d Lt, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Cyber Flight Commander</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Communications Squadron&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>donovk5@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(847) 682-0262</p>', 11, 38, '2019-09-13 14:28:15', NULL),
('Recruitment Opportunities', 'Recruitment Opportunities', '<p><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #626f82; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; background-color: #f7f7f7;\">Cadets,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #626f82; background-color: #f7f7f7;\">There are several opportunities to recruit for the detachment coming up in September that would greatly benefit everyone. I have attached a spreadsheet for all who are interested.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: #f7f7f7; color: #065d8a; outline: 0px;\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1ho05cRikBcTfm4eMgtyJzd4c-0DhwIAsBHKqEUh_cqc/edit?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1ho05cRikBcTfm4eMgtyJzd4c-0DhwIAsBHKqEUh_cqc/edit?usp=sharing</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Very Respectfully,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">IAN A. MORIARTY, C/2d Lt, AFROTC</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Special Projects Flight Commander</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">550th AFROTC Mission Support Group</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">moriai@rpi.edu</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 20, 39, '2019-09-15 17:56:19', NULL),
('Cornell Drill Meet', 'Cornell Drill Meet', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Cornell Military Excellence Competition is coming up soon and will be held on 19 October 2019. The events that you can sign up for are the 4x400 relay, 5K run, Ironman, 4x100 freestyle swim, 4x100 IM relay, and a 50 yard indiviual freestyle swim. There is also a Fitness Medley and the explanation for this can be found on the link below. Please take a look at the spreadsheet and fill out what events you want to do by October 2nd COB so I can pass along the information to Cornell. For transportation, you will have to figure out a carpool to get to Cornell. We have had great participation at the Cornell Meet in the past so lets keep that up this year.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1nZcC3PA3FETqqJgBepC5fKhhLc-Ed7acBjS8BRl3Q4k/edit?usp=sharing\">Sign-Up Sheet</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1s0XWctY0nl7OBFrnHCVjaHTcPVX2ddWtWCMIzRAeAHc/edit?usp=sharing\">Fitness Medley Description</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>BAILEY E. DAIGLE, C/2d Lt, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Cadet Drill Advisor</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Cadet Wing</p>\r\n<p>daiglb@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(518)742-0980)</p>', 40, 40, '2019-09-16 13:58:58', NULL);
