('October Recruiting Events', 'October Recruiting Events', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Several new volunteering opportunities are now available in October.&nbsp; The detachment is holding several recruiting events and we can use all the help that we can get!&nbsp; Please if you are interested in attending one of these recruiting events put your name in the Google Sheet that I have attached ASAP.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1vIc5PKw2GaWylRQ2asJYw5MIvgpdTcymKEHQCuHpbbs/edit?usp=sharing\">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1vIc5PKw2GaWylRQ2asJYw5MIvgpdTcymKEHQCuHpbbs/edit?usp=sharing</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>JAMES W. HOFMANN, C/3C, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Special Projects Flight</p>\r\n<p>hofmaj2@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(518) 925-0570</p>', 13, 74, '2019-10-02 20:12:33', NULL),
('Guest Speaker', 'Guest Speaker', '<p>Cadets,<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><br />On Friday 11 October at 1645, we will be having a retired pilot with manned and unmanned flight time coming to speak to the Detachment.&nbsp; The speaker also spent some time in Air Force engineering, so he can answer some questions on that as well.&nbsp; This is a non-mandatory event, but if you plan on attending, please click Read and Understood on this message by COB Sunday.<br /><br /><br />Very Respectfully,<br /><br />ALEXANDER T. FERENCZHALMY, C/3C, AFROTC<br /><br />Public Affairs Flight<br /><br />550th AFROTC Communications Squadron<br /><br />ferena@rpi.edu<br /><br />(575) 921-9403</p>', 14, 76, '2019-10-03 20:41:50', NULL),
('Lounge Flight Sim + VR Up and Running', 'Lounge Flight Sim + VR', '<p>Cadets,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Lounge Flight Sim + VR is currently up and running! As of right now, War Thunder is downloading and should be up by tomorrow evening, however, I did purchase Beatsaber as a little gift to all of you so after hours feel free to check it out!</p>\r\n<p>Remember this equipment is expensive and has been an ongoing project to allocate funds and complete. Be respectful of the equipment and if you are unsure of how to work anything please shoot me a message. In addition, if you have any suggestions for games or have any software for the sim, please let me know. I will be in the lounge tomorrow afternoon/evening to show people the ropes if is their first time trying VR.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>--&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>KATHERINE G. DONOVAN, C/2d Lt, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Cyber Flight Commander</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Communications Squadron&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>donovk5@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(847) 682-0262</p>', 11, 77, '2019-10-03 21:21:43', NULL),
('Schindler\'s School of Swiftness', 'First Workout This Week', '<p>Cadets,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>SSS is starting this week! I hope to see many of you Tuesday at 1700. We will be meeting in the lounge and running to harkness for the workout:</p>\r\n<p>The workout is called a 5-4-3-2-1. It will consist of periods of timed interval running for the formentioned time, it\'s a tough workout but of course can be done at you own pace.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Additionally in the future I would like to use the group function on the website to send out info about SSS, so if you show up to the workout or send me an&nbsp;<strong>EMAIL</strong> about being added to the list.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>SPENCER C. SCHINDLER, C/Lt Col, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Operations Group Commander</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Operations Group&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>schins@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(845)417-6930</p>', 43, 78, '2019-10-07 10:03:55', NULL),
('LLAB 6', 'LLAB 6', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Operation:&nbsp;<strong>\"Who\'s In Charge?\"</strong></p>\r\n<p>Date:&nbsp;<strong>9 October</strong></p>\r\n<p>Location:&nbsp;<strong>LOW 4050</strong></p>\r\n<p>Time:&nbsp;<strong>0800</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">UOD:&nbsp; The Uniform of the Day (UOD) will be the </span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Airman Battle Uniform</span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> (ABU).&nbsp; Cadets who have not been issued the ABUs will wear </span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Black Polo and Khakis </span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(BPaK) or </span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Detachment Polo and Khakis </span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(DetPaK).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">OPORD: <a title=\"LLAB 6 OPORD\" href=\"https://rpi.box.com/s/sa7s94d3jxf2rtelxq6isiwa5bjudmr4\">Link</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #404040; font-family: Arial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Very Respectfully,</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MATTHEW R. BATCHELOR, C/3C, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Alpha Flight</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Training Squadron</p>\r\n<p>batchm@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(541) 913-0030</p>', 45, 79, '2019-10-07 13:22:57', NULL),
('PT 12', 'PT 12', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>PT 12 will be on Wednesday, 9 October, from 0630 to 0730. This is a track workout, so effective stretching and water will be important.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>OPORD: <a title=\"PT 12 OPORD\" href=\"https://rpi.box.com/s/sa7s94d3jxf2rtelxq6isiwa5bjudmr4\">Link</a></p>\r\n<p>Location: Harkness Track and Field</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>MATTHEW R. BATCHELOR, C/3C, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Alpha Flight</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Training Squadron</p>\r\n<p>batchm@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(541) 913-0030</p>', 45, 80, '2019-10-07 14:24:20', NULL),
('Fall Lounge Cleaning', 'Fall Lounge Cleaning', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It has been brought to the attention of MWR that the cadet lounge is being abused, this is a shared space that all cadets should have the ability to use. <strong>EVERYONE is responsible to clean the lounge!</strong> You can pick up trash, put away controllers, hang up fallen jackets, ect. regardless of if it is your group responsible for cleaning that week. The scheduled mentor chain is responsible for vacuuming, picking up trash, collecting abandoned items in the lost and found, organizing game consoles once during that week. Once the lounge is cleaned, one member of the group is required to send me a photo by COB Friday.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Starting 9 October 2019 there will be a designated lost and found box which will be donated to goodwill or thrown away on the last day of every month as well as a vacuum.</p>\r\n<p>This week mentor chain 3, is responsible for cleaning. Please refer to the Detachment 550 google calendar to view the schedule of the rest of the semester. Review mentor chains <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1s6xoAGfQcGlQuAREiQWP6rmoUvS33VyLVOymR4al8R8/edit?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>, all chains have been updated, if you cannot find your name please contact me.</p>\r\n<p>Once you have reviewed this post, click \"read and understood,\" Please respect this space before we lose the privilege of using it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>V/R</p>\r\n<p>HANNAH J. ENGGASSER, C/2nd Lt., AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Commander, MWR Flight</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Support Squadron</p>\r\n<p>enggah@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(215) 313-9983</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 74, 81, '2019-10-07 18:37:25', NULL),
('PT 13', 'PT 13', '<p>Cadets,<br /><br /><br />PT 13 will be taking place on Thursday, 10 October at Harkness Field from 0630-0730.&nbsp; The Uniform of the Day (UOD) will be the Airman Battle Uniform (ABU) or Physical Training Gear (PTG) for cadets who do not have ABUs.&nbsp; We will be completing a ruck workout, so please remember to stretch and hydrate appropriately beforehand.<br /><br /><br />Very Respectfully,<br /><br />ALEXANDER T. FERENCZHALMY, C/3C, AFROTC<br /><br />Alpha Flight<br /><br />550th AFROTC Training Squadron<br /><br />ferena@rpi.edu&nbsp;<br /><br />(575) 921-9403</p>', 14, 82, '2019-10-07 22:13:14', NULL);
