('Updated Standardization', 'LLAB Standardization', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>From now on you will be expected to have the following on you at all times during LLAB.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Something to write with\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pen&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Pencil</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Something to write on\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A small notebook that will fit in your pocket&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>A peice of paper&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>RPI ID</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you do not have the following items you will submit a memo up your respective chain of command as to why you did not come prepared.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: #ffffff;\">Read and Understood by: 10 October 2019</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; font-size: 16px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">--</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/Lt Col, AFROTC</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">Inspector General</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">550th Training Squadron</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\"><a href=\"mailto:messaj@rpi.edu\">messaj@rpi.edu</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">(585) 500-9728</p>', 2, 84, '2019-10-08 22:49:22', NULL),
('MWR Apple Picking', 'MWR Apple Picking', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MWR is organizing an apple picking event for this Saturday, 12 October 2019. Cadets interested in attending should sign up to carpool <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1CqqY98wuW79YUV3hUZmIjWK5NwkYqsDHRr43Gztm_Ag/edit?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a> and meet in the cadet lounge to leave by 1100 on Saturday morning. For cadet planning to drive from another location, we will be arriving at the orchard around 1130. We will be going to Bowman Orchard which has a $5 entrance fee and then an additional cost of $1.60 per lb of apples.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>HANNAH J. ENGGASSER, C/2nd Lt., AFROTC</p>\r\n<p>Deputy, Bravo Flight</p>\r\n<p>550th AFROTC Training Squadron</p>\r\n<p>enggah@rpi.edu</p>\r\n<p>(215)313-9983</p>', 74, 85, '2019-10-09 16:45:18', NULL),
('Joint Service Family Weekend', 'Food, Football, and Fun', '<p>Cadets,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On the 19th of October, the Joint Service Representatives will be hosting a Family Weekend. There will be a free BBQ, snacks, and a cross-branch flag football game and you are all encouraged to bring your family members.</p>\r\n<p>If you would like to volunteer for the snack bar or participate in the flag football game, go to the Google Sheet below to sign up. You do not need to volunteer or play to attend. However, we need 11 players on our team to play in the football game and 2 volunteers for the snack bar. Please participate so the event can run smoothly and so we can show the Army and Navy that we are the stronger branch.<br />https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1NEduJq5yN35GO6RFnllnkWFcD8tukl3ty8MOBJVLzj0/edit?usp=sharing</p>\r\n<p>I hope to see you all there.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Very Respectfully,</p>\r\n<p>ERJIN CHOI, C/2d Lt, AFROTC<br />Joint Service Representative<br />550th AFROTC Cadet Wing<br />choie@rpi.edu<br />(516)840-1288</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 33, 86, '2019-10-11 01:30:42', NULL),
