	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0in;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--> <!--StartFragment--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: right;\" align=\"right\">29 August 2019<span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MEMORANDUM FOR<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>CW/CC<span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">FROM:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>C/Lt Col Joseph Messare</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">SUBJECT:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Detachment Attendance Policy Fall 2019</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">1. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>This memorandum will outline the Fall 2019 Attendance Policy for Detachment 550. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">2. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Cadets must make on-time attendance at all mandatory Air Force Reserve Officers&rsquo; Training Corps (AFROTC) events a top priority. These events include Physical Training (PT) and Leadership Laboratory (LLAB). Military Personnel Flight (MPF) is tasked with tracking attendance of each mandatory event using the website</span>. This will be considered the official attendance so if you are not marked as present it will be treated as if you did not attend the event.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>In the event that the website does not accurately reflect your attendance you must email a member of MPF in order to make the correction by Close of Business (1700, COB) Sunday for an event in the previous week.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">3. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>All cadets must attend at least 80% of all mandatory AFROTC events. For example, if 28 PTs are scheduled, a cadet must make at least 23 PTs. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">a. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Cadets who receive one unexcused absence from LLAB will be informally counseled by their immediate superior and must submit an Official Memorandum (OM) to their immediate superior to document their absence. Cadets who receive two unexcused absences from LLAB will be formally counseled by their immediate superior, as well as the superior&rsquo;s immediate superior, and must submit an OM to the IG to document their absence. For example, if the Alpha Flight Commander missed two LLABs, they will be formally counseled by the Training Squadron Commander and the Operations Group Commander. Cadets who receive three unexcused absences from LLAB will be formally counseled by the Operations Group Commander, IG, and Director of Operations (DO) and must again submit an OM to the IG for documentation. Further unexcused absences may result in the cadet failing to meet AFROTC retention standards. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">b. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Cadets who receive two unexcused absences from PT will be informally counseled by their immediate superior and must submit an OM to their immediate superior to document their absence. Cadets who receive three unexcused absences from PT will be formally counseled by their immediate superior, as well as the superior&rsquo;s immediate superior, and must submit an OM to the IG to document their absence. Cadets with four unexcused absences from PT will be formally counseled by the IG, and must again submit an OM to the IG. Cadets with five unexcused absences from PT will be formally counseled by the IG and DO, and must again submit an OM to the IG. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">4. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>A cadet looking to be categorized as excused for a specific event must complete an OM at least 48 hours prior to the intended event. The OM will be sent up to the DO via their chain-of-</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"page-break-before: always;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">command. Excusal requests such as family emergencies, personal sickness, personal injury, and inclement weather day-of are potential grounds for event excusal. It is important to note that excusal requests are not limited to these circumstances. Cadets encountering unexpected circumstances must notify their immediate supervisor of their attendance status as soon as possible. If the reason is medically related, a cadet needs to attach a physician signed Medical Visit Form (MVF), or equivalent, to their Excusal OM. Absences due to oversleeping or unexplained tardiness will not be granted excusal from the event. Excused absences will not be factored into the attendance requirement; cadets must still attend at least 80% of events not excused. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">5. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Cadets are expected to arrive No Later Than (NLT) 10 minutes prior to the start of all mandatory events. An OPORD may specify an earlier NLT time, however, later NLT times will not be acknowledged by the IG. Any cadets arriving past the NLT time will be marked tardy for that event. For example, if the NLT time is 0750, any cadet arriving at 0750 is on time and any cadet arriving at or after 0751 is tardy. Cadets who receive three tardy designations to any mandatory events will be informally counseled by their immediate superior and must submit an OM explaining how they will fix the issue to their immediate superior. Cadets who receive four tardy designations will be formally counseled by their immediate superior, as well as the superior&rsquo;s immediate superior, and must submit an OM to the IG to document their tardiness. Cadets tardy five or more times to any event within one semester will be formally counseled by the IG and DO, and must submit an OM to the IG to document their tardiness. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">6. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Should a mandatory event be canceled and not rescheduled, cadets will be given the opportunity to make up the event. For PT, cadets in need of a make-up will either: perform PT individually and submit a workout description to be approved by the lettered Flight Commander in charge of PT that week; or attend a Supplemental PT session, should one be offered. Making up missed LLABs will be determined on a case-by-case basis. Upon completion, the cadet must submit an OM to officially document the make-up. The OM must be received by the DO via the chain-of-command within one week of the event. Failure to submit an OM on time will result in the event being marked as an unexcused absence. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\">7.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Cadets are ultimately responsible for their own attendance and consequently must ensure that they are completing the proper paperwork should they be tardy or receive an unexcused absence.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">8.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>If you have any questions regarding this memorandum, please contact me by email at messaj@rpi.edu or by phone at (585)-500-9728.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: 328.5pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin-left: 3.0in;\"><span style=\"color: windowtext;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>//JWM/29AUG19/SIGNED//</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin-left: 3.0in;\"><span style=\"color: #00000a;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/Lt Col, AFROTC</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin-left: 3.0in;\"><span style=\"color: #00000a;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Inspector General</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 3.0in;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>550th AFROTC Operations Group</p>\r\n<p><!--EndFragment--></p>', 3, '2020-01-10 05:05:01', NULL);
