so-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0in;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--> <!--StartFragment--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: right;\" align=\"right\">29 August 2019<span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MEMORANDUM FOR<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>CW/CC<span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">FROM:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>C/Lt Col Joseph Messare<span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">SUBJECT:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Detachment Suspense Policy Fall 2019</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">1. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>This memorandum will outline the Spring 2019 Suspense Policy for Detachment 550.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">2. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Suspenses are essential for effective communication within the wing. A set deadline for</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">accomplishing tasks ensures efficient and organized completion of mission-essential activities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">Meeting each suspense is important not only for unit function, but as preparation for entrance</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">into Active Duty. The Inspector General (IG) is tasked with enforcing this policy and actions</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">taken should a suspense be missed are outlined below.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">3. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Cadre-set suspenses are to be considered top priority for all cadets. These suspenses are</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">frequently time-sensitive and impact a more significant audience should they be missed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">Therefore, missing a cadre-set suspense will result in a more serious response. In an event where</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">a cadet fails to meet a cadre-set suspense, the cadet will be formally counseled by the Director of</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">Operations (DO). He/she must complete an Official Memorandum (OM) explaining why he/she</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">had not completed the work by the set suspense. The cadet must submit this OM to the IG</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">within 24 hours of being counseled.</p>\r\n<p>4. Cadet-set suspenses are generally more frequent than cadre-set suspenses. With this in mind, cadet-set work is more likely to be overlooked or forgotten.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>a. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Cadet-set squadron/flight or subordinate suspenses are to be set no later than 48 hour before the due date. Declaring a missed suspense under these circumstances is at the discretion of the IG. Use common sense when delegating a large amount of work in a short amount of time.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>b. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Cadet-set suspenses that are not Wing, group, or squadron specific but are specific to a</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">particular organization (i.e. AAS, AS100, etc.) must follow the same 72-hour rule. Within 24</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">hours of the suspense, the post must be reposted or resent.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>c. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Cadet-set suspenses between flights must be clearly set at least 72 hours in advance. For</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">example, if Alpha Flight sets a suspense for Bravo Flight, it must be 72 hours minimum before</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">the deadline.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>d. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Any suspense which does not follow the above procedures will not be justification for</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">corrective measure detailed in section 5 unless the cadet given the suspense agrees to complete</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">the task under the illegal suspense. These situations will be handled on a case by case basis.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">5. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Response procedures for missed cadet-set suspenses will follow a 4-tiered system with an</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">optional verbal warning at the discretion of the cadet who set the suspense for first time</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">offenders. All OMs must include details of when the suspense was set for and how long the</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">cadet had to complete the suspense. It should also include the nature of the actual offense and</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">what corrective measures are being taken to ensure the offense is not repeated.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>a. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Tier 1: In the event a cadet fails to meet a cadet-set suspense, his/her immediate superior</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">will conduct an informal counseling with that cadet. The cadet will then submit an OM to</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">his/her immediate superior within 24 hours of the counseling.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>b. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Tier 2: After a second offense, the cadet will receive a formal counseling from their</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">immediate superior and submit an OM to their immediate superior within 24 hours of the</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">counseling.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>c. Tier 3: After a third offense, the cadet&rsquo;s immediate superior will provide the IG with an</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">OM detailing the nature of the third offense and the OMs from the first and second offense. The</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">IG will then conduct a formal counseling with the cadet and the cadet&rsquo;s immediate superior. The</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">cadet will complete an OM within 24 hours of the counseling and submit it to the IG directly.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>d. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Tier 4: Beyond three offenses, the cadet&rsquo;s immediate superior will provide the IG with</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">another OM detailing the most recent offense. The IG will notify the Cadet Wing Commander</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">(CC/CW) and the DO. The cadet will be subject to reprimand from the cadre chain-of command.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>e. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>The term &ldquo;immediate superior&rdquo; refers to the cadet who delegated the task. For example, a</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">cadet may be in Alpha Flight as well as Morale Welfare and Recreation (MWR) Flight. If the</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">MWR Flight Commander delegates a task and the cadet misses the suspense, any relevant</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">paperwork and counseling will be given to or handled by the MWR Flight Commander. The</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">Alpha Flight Commander may be notified of the missed suspense, but will not be involved in any</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">disciplinary action in this case.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>f. Regarding suspenses between flights, the Flight Commander is ultimately responsible for</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">the completion of the suspense, and therefore will write any OMs and receive any counselings.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">6. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Any Practical Military Training (PMT) conducted off Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute&rsquo;s campus must be populated in the cadre calendar at least one month in advance.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">7.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>If you have any questions regarding this memorandum, please contact me by email at messaj@rpi.edu or by phone at (585)-500-9728.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: 328.5pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin-left: 3.0in;\"><span style=\"color: windowtext;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>//JWM/29AUG19/SIGNED//</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin-left: 3.0in;\"><span style=\"color: #00000a;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>JOSEPH W. MESSARE, C/Lt Col, AFROTC</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin-left: 3.0in;\"><span style=\"color: #00000a;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Inspector General</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 3.0in;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>550th AFROTC Operations Group</p>\r\n<p><!--EndFragment--></p>', 4, '2020-01-10 05:05:01', NULL);
INSERT INTO `wiki` (`name`, `body`, `id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
('Warrior Knowledge', '<p><strong>Mission Statements, Honor Code and Values</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>AIR FORCE MISSION:</strong></span> TO FLY, FIGHT AND WIN IN AIR, SPACE, AND CYBERSPACE.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>HOLM CENTER MISSION:</strong></span> WE BUILD LEADERS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">AFROTC MISSION:</span> </strong>DEVELOPING LEADERS OF CHARACTER FOR TOMORROW&rsquo;S AIR FORCE.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>CADET HONOR CODE:</strong></span> WE WILL NOT LIE, STEAL, OR CHEAT, NOR TOLERATE AMONG US ANYONE WHO DOES</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>CORE VALUES:</strong></span> INTEGRITY FIRST, SERVICE BEFORE SELF, EXCELLENCE IN ALL WE DO</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The Air Force Code of Conduct</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>I.</strong><br />I am an American, fighting in the forces which guard my country and our way of life. I am prepared to give my life in their defense.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>II.</strong><br />I will never surrender of my own free will. If in command, I will never surrender the members of my command while they still have the means to resist.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>III.</strong><br />If I am captured, I will continue to resist by all means available. I will make every effort to escape and aid others to escape. I will accept neither parole nor special favors from the enemy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>IV.</strong><br />If I become a prisoner of war, I will keep faith with my fellow prisoners. I will give no information nor take part in any action which might be harmful to my comrades. If I am senior I will take command. If not I will obey the lawful orders of those appointed over me and back them up in every way.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>V.</strong><br />When questioned, should I become a prisoner of war, I am required to give name, rank, service number, and date of birth. I will evade answering further questions to the utmost of my ability. I will make no oral or written statements disloyal to my country and its allies or harmful to their cause.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>VI.</strong><br />I will never forget that I am an American, fighting for freedom, responsible for my actions, and dedicated to the principles which made my country free. I will trust in my God and in the United States of America.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The Airman&rsquo;s Creed</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I AM AN AMERICAN AIRMAN.<br />I AM A WARRIOR<br />I HAVE ANSWERED MY NATION&rsquo;S CALL.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />I AM AN AMERICAN AIRMAN.<br />MY MISSION IS TO FLY, FIGHT AND WIN.<br />I AM FAITHFUL TO A PROUD HERITAGE,<br />A TRADITION OF HONOR,<br />AND A LEGACY OF VALOR.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />I AM AN AMERICAN AIRMAN,<br />GUARDIAN OF FREEDOM AND JUSTICE,<br />MY NATION&rsquo;S SWORD AND SHIELD,<br />ITS SENTRY AND AVENGER.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />I DEFEND MY COUNTRY WITH MY LIFE.<br />I AM AN AMERICAN AIRMAN:<br />WINGMAN, LEADER, WARRIOR.<br />I WILL NEVER LEAVE AN AIRMAN BEHIND,<br />I WILL NEVER FALTER,<br />AND I WILL NOT FAIL.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The Air Force Song</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Off we go into the wild blue yonder,<br />Climbing high into the sun;<br />Here they come zooming to meet our thunder,<br />At &lsquo;em boys, give&lsquo;er the gun!<br />Down we dive, spouting our flame from under,<br />Off with one helluva roar;<br />We live in fame or go down in flame. Hey!<br />Nothing&rsquo;ll stop the U.S. Air Force!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />Minds of men fashioned a crate of thunder,<br />Sent it high into the blue;<br />Hands of men blasted the world asunder;<br />How they lived God only knew!<br />Souls of men dreaming of skies to conquer<br />Gave us wings, ever to soar!<br />With scouts before and bombers galore. Hey!<br />Nothing&rsquo;ll stop the U.S. Air Force!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />Here&rsquo;s a toast to the host<br />Of those who love the vastness of the sky,<br />To a friend we send a message of his brother men who fly.<br />We drink to those who gave their all of old,<br />Then down we roar to score the rainbow&rsquo;s pot of gold.<br />A toast to the host of men we boast, the U.S. Air Force!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />Off we go into the wild sky yonder,<br />Keep the wings level and true;<br />If you&rsquo;d live to be a gray-haired wonder<br />Keep the nose out of the blue!<br />Flying men, guarding the nation&rsquo;s border,<br />We&rsquo;ll be there, followed by more!<br />In echelon we carry on. Hey!<br />Nothing&rsquo;ll stop the U.S. Air Force!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Chain of Command</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><a class=\"SetPageTerm-wordText\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">President/Commander in Chief</span></a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">The Honorable Donald J. Trump</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Secretary of</span><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\"> Defense </span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a class=\"SetPageTerm-definitionText\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">The Honorable Dr. Mark T Esper</span></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Secretary of the Air Force</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">The Honorable Matthew P. Donovan<br /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Air Force Chief of Staff</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">General David L. Goldfein<br /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">AETC Commander</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Lieutenant General Marshall B. Webb</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Air University Commander</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Major General Brad M. Sullivan<br /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Holm Center Commander</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\"><span id=\"contnetStyle\">Brigadier General Christopher J. Niemi</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">AFROTC Commander</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\"><span id=\"contnetStyle\">Colonel Christopher L. Bennet<br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Northeast Region Commander</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Colonel Thomas A. Bongiovi</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">DET 550 Commander</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"TermText notranslate lang-en\">Lieutenant Colonel Nicholas C. Graham</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Operations Flight Commander</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Major Cooper W. Steele</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Acronyms</strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 1012px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">ABU</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Airman Battle Uniform</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet Flt/AO</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Flight Academics Officer</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet Flt/CC</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Flight Commander</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet Flt/CD</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Deputy Flight Commander</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet Flt/D&amp;C</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Flight Drill &amp; Ceremonies Officer</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet Flt/PFO</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Flight Physical Fitness Officer</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet Flt/STANDO</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Flight Standardization Officer</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet GP/AO</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Group Academic Officer</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet GP/CC</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Group Commander</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; height: 22px;\">Cadet GP/D&amp;C</td>\r\n<td sty